 "cells": [

   "id": "b16fe0bc-fb83-427b-86f4-57e938793394",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Introduction to PyCBA\n",
    "\n",
    "PyCBA (Python Continuous Beam Analysis) is a general linear elastic one-dimensional beam analysis package.\n",
    "\n",
    "This introduction demonstrates the basic use of `PyCBA` and results that can be obtained. So let's get started..."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "20efbbf0-8959-40ac-ace9-dc3bc0e39776",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Basic imports\n",
    "import pycba as cba  # The main package\n",
    "import numpy as np  # For arrays\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt  # For plotting\n",
    "from IPython import display  # For images in this notebook"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2c503d16-6fb1-448c-b767-21cab9b6abee",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Example 1 - Basic Analysis\n",
    "Analyse a two span beam, with a UDL of 20 kN/m on each span"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "3fd66b54-a54a-413a-832c-bf8fd7ee4a7e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Image object>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "width": 800
      }
     },
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "display.Image(\"./images/intro_ex_1.png\",width=800)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "64d15114-4b3a-45b6-bd2a-3116b070c907",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here is the specification for `PyCBA`, explained below:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "fb6911be-79e7-445d-8a7e-941947e6a382",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "L = [7.5, 7.0]\n",
    "EI = 30 * 600e7 * 1e-6\n",
    "R = [-1, 0, -1, 0, -1, 0]\n",
    "LM = [[1, 1, 20, 0, 0], [2, 1, 20, 0, 0]]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d922ddbb-f5c2-4ecd-ad0f-f60abaa55446",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Initially, we define the member lengths, which in this case coincides with the spans, $AB$, and $BC$. \n",
    "\n",
    "The flexural rigidity (elastic modulus multiplied by the second moment of area) can be defined for each member, or if a scalar value is passed, this is assigned to all members. Here we take $E = 30$ GPa and $I = 600 \\times 10^7$ mm$^4$, and apply a conversion to put it into a consistent set of units (kN and m).\n",
    "\n",
    "The beam restraints at each nodal degree of freedom are then defined. Since there are three nodes, this will be a vector of $2 \\times 3 = 6$ entries. Only the vertical (and not rotational) degree of freedom is restrained at nodes $A$, $B$, and $C$, and so this is indicated using $-1$ and $0$ for unrestrained.\n",
    "\n",
    "Finally, the load matrix is defined, which is a list of loads, where each load is defined by a list of five numbers, as defined in the docs:\n",
    "```\n",
    "Span No. | Load Type | Load Value | Distance a | Load Cover c\n",
    "```\n",
    "For UDLs covering the full length of the member, only the span number, load type, and value have non-zero entries.\n",
    "\n",
    "With the basic variables defined, we construct the `beam_analysis` object by passing these variables, we then call the `analyze()` function and plot the results:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "c352c479-a619-48f2-8c38-7982cfac16a0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "beam_analysis = cba.BeamAnalysis(L, EI, R, LM)\n",
    "beam_analysis.analyze()\n",
    "beam_analysis.plot_results()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0a4bb6fa-903a-4dd2-8cc6-ee3c1ceb99c5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The numerical results can found from the `beam_results` member of `beam_analysis` object.\n",
    "\n",
    "For example, the reactions corresponding to the fully-restrained nodes are:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "a725b6b2-724b-4c2d-bdec-35fea715dcab",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "array([ 57.41666667, 181.42261905,  51.16071429])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "beam_analysis.beam_results.R"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2239b7d1-0d3c-46f8-ab92-cd9f4a1aca04",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "and the maximum bending moment along the second member, $BC$, can be got from:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "f00f5956-64fd-45f7-b433-9a2a6a3221d9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "65.42525"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "beam_analysis.beam_results.vRes[1].M.max()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c3dfc141-6a34-446f-8de7-55102682e3aa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Since we have been consistent with our units, the reactions are in kN and the bending moment in kNm."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c3eff95b-5611-4790-961b-9ce674068176",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Example 2 - Load Definitions\n",
    "\n",
    "In this example, we consider a two-span beam with a fixed remote end, and more load types."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "1a3feabd-f760-4e9b-b57a-442fe92ca43a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Image object>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "width": 800
      }
     },
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "display.Image(\"./images/intro_ex_2.png\",width=800)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "71686aa9-1944-4d53-a5a8-e4f89e096587",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "With two loads the *load matrix* (see `pycba.load`) is a list of two lists:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Span 1: point load is load type 2, with a value of $50$ kN, at $a = 3$ m\n",
    "- Span 2: moment load is load type 4, anti-clockwise positive $50$ kNm, at $a = 4$ m\n",
    "\n",
    "Note, also that node $C$ will have its two degrees of freedom restrained."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "70433eb3-7534-4c45-9a58-6969ea1889e6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "L = [10.0, 10.0]\n",
    "EI = 30 * 600e7 * 1e-6  # kNm2\n",
    "R = [-1, 0, -1, 0, -1, -1]\n",
    "LM = [[1, 2, 50, 3, 0], [2, 4, 50, 4, 0]]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "aa075ee1-a081-464d-93f2-00686ef479ab",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And to better evaluate the discontinuities for the moment and point loads, we can increase the number of evaluation points along each member to 500 when calling `analyze()` as follows:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "880940b2-f623-45e2-bae0-552ea64bd922",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "beam_analysis = cba.BeamAnalysis(L, EI, R, LM)\n",
    "beam_analysis.analyze(500)\n",
    "beam_analysis.plot_results()"
   ]
  }
 ],
